
@startuml
' Class Diagram for Appointment Management System

class Student {
  -studentID: String
  -name: String
  -registeredCourses: List<Course>
}

class TeachingAssistant {
  -taID: String
  -name: String
  -teachingCourses: List<Course>
}

class Course {
  -courseID: String
  -title: String
  -description: String
}

class Appointment {
  -appointmentID: String
  -date: Date
  -time: Time
  -duration: Integer
  -student: Student
  -teachingAssistant: TeachingAssistant
  -course: Course
}

Student "1" --> "0..*" Course : registeredFor
TeachingAssistant "1" --> "0..*" Course : teaches
Appointment "1" --> "1" Student : student
Appointment "1" --> "1" TeachingAssistant : teachingAssistant
Appointment "1" --> "1" Course : course

note right of Appointment
  An appointment is always for one specific course and with one TA.
end note
@enduml

### Explanation:
- **Student**: Can request appointments only for courses they are registered in.
- **TeachingAssistant (TA)**: Can only provide help for courses they teach.
- **Course**: Has a unique ID, title, and description.
- **Appointment**: Links a student, a teaching assistant, and a course. Each appointment is associated with exactly one student, one TA, and one course.

